    <para id="id1172523303719">As a consequence of the stability of M<sup>+</sup>, the Group 1 metals have the least variation in chemistry of the any Group in the periodic table. The only exceptions are the subtle trends that exist for lithium due to its small size (<link target-id="id7918480"/>). All of the metals are more electropositive than hydrogen (<link target-id="id7005236"/>).  </para>
