      <para id="id1172523507669">The ratio of the ionic radii (r<sup>+</sup>/r<sup>-</sup>) neatly defines the structural type observed for alkali metal salts (<link target-id="id1172523482627"/>). The unit cells for ZnS (zinc blende), NaCl (rock salt), and CsCl are shown in <link target-id="id1172523521434"/>, <link target-id="id6833173"/>, and <link target-id="id5108770"/>, respectively. </para>
